</section>
<!-- ════════ GLOSSARY & RESOURCES ════════ -->
<section id="glossary">
  <div class="cgp-container">
    <p class="section-kicker fade-in">Reference</p>
    <h2 class="section-title fade-in">Glossary &amp; resources</h2>
    <div class="grid grid-2 fade-in" style="align-items:start;">
      <div class="card">
        <h4>📖 Glossary</h4>
        <dl class="glossary">
          <dt>Theme</dt><dd>A coordinated set of colors, fonts, and effects (plus background). Portable as .thmx.</dd>
          <dt>Slide Master</dt><dd>The top-level blueprint slide; parent of all layouts. Holds global elements.</dd>
          <dt>Layout</dt><dd>A child blueprint for one slide type, defining its placeholder arrangement.</dd>
          <dt>Placeholder</dt><dd>A pre-formatted content container added in Slide Master view.</dd>
          <dt>Template (.potx)</dt><dd>The saved, reusable package of theme + master + layouts + sample slides.</dd>
          <dt>Sample slide</dt><dd>A finished example slide saved in the template; Copilot's primary learning signal.</dd>
          <dt>Brand Kit</dt><dd>The Copilot rule layer governing colors, fonts, voice, logos, and approved imagery.</dd>
          <dt>Brand Checker</dt><dd>The Copilot tool that flags and fixes brand violations in generated decks (PowerPoint only).</dd>
          <dt>OAL</dt><dd>Organization Asset Library — the SharePoint-based store that distributes templates.</dd>
          <dt>Content density</dt><dd>How much content a slide holds — light, medium, or heavy.</dd>
          <dt>WCAG AA</dt><dd>4.5:1 contrast for normal text, 3:1 for large text.</dd>
        </dl>
      </div>
